      • iterator

        java.util.Iterator<Statistics> iterator()
        Return an iterator over team members in the roster.

        The iterator returns objects that implement the Statistics interface.

        The set of statistics are unordered.

        Returns:
        Iterator iterator for roster

      • iterator

        java.util.Iterator<Statistics> iterator​(java.util.Comparator<Statistics> comparator)
        Return an iterator over the roster, sorted according the Comparator.

        The iterator returns objects that implement the Statistics interface.

        The iteration order is determined by the comparator (least first).

        The comparator may assume that its arguments implement Statistics.

        Parameters:
        comparator - determines the order of the set of statistics returned.
        Returns:
        Iterator sorted iterator for team roster
